article.description: — Cameron Tyson's 22 points helped Seattle U defeat Southern Utah 73-63 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Tyson scores 22 in Seattle U's 73-63 victory over Southern Utah
article.linkText: Tyson scores 22 in Seattle U's 73-63 victory over Southern Utah
article.story: SEATTLE -- — Cameron Tyson's 22 points helped Seattle U defeat Southern Utah 73-63 on Saturday night. Tyson added five rebounds for the Redhawks (5-3). Brandton Chatfield scored 18 points while finishing 9 of 13 from the floor, and added eight rebounds. Alex Schumacher was 3 of 11 shooting and 8 of 10 from the free throw line to finish with 14 points, while adding eight assists and three steals. The Thunderbirds (2-5) were led by Zion Young, who recorded 14 points. Prophet Johnson added 12 points for Southern Utah. Chazz Hutchison also had 11 points and two blocks. NEXT UP Seattle U next plays Saturday against Northwest (WA) at home, and Southern Utah will visit Utah on Tuesday. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
